Names:
-Gabriella: God is my strength
Raphaela: A feminine form of Raphael, the archangel associated with healing, itâ€™s perfect for a savior figure.
Cassiel: Known as an angel of solitude and tears, Cassiel could represent an angel with a more mysterious or introspective role.
-Leila: Meaning "night," it can symbolize an angel who guides people through darkness toward the light.
-Eliana: Meaning "God has answered," it has a gentle, divine resonance fitting for an angelic mission.
Auriel: A variation of Uriel, an angel of light, this name carries a sense of divine illumination.
Amara: Meaning "grace" or "immortal," it brings a sense of eternity and divine kindness.
Seren: Meaning "star," this celestial name can represent guidance from the heavens.
-Talia: Meaning "dew from heaven," it evokes a soft, nurturing image, fitting for a heavenly protector.
Seraphina: Derived from "seraphim," a type of angel, it evokes a sense of divine light and purity.
Celestia: Meaning "heavenly" or "of the sky," it aligns with the celestial theme.
Evangeline: Meaning "bearer of good news," it fits the theme of angels sent to save and guide.
Ariel: Known as a name of an angel and meaning "lion of God," it carries a strong yet heavenly tone.
Selaphiel: A traditional angelic name, meaning "prayer of God," it connects well with the mission of saving souls.

